<subSubSection lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="63" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1193,1979]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[245,377,1332,1356]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">Description</emphasis>
. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation box="[549,608,1332,1355]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1673,1696]" captionTargetBox="[211,1370,260,1552]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,194,1649]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Megarthrus andinus sp. nov. Habitus (scale bar = 1 mm) (1); antenna (2); medial process of abdominal sternites II and III, in lateral view (anterior to left) (3); male sternite VIII, dissected (4); ventral (5) and lateral (6) aedeagus; female sternite VIII (7); ventral (8) and lateral (9) female genital segment (scale bars = 0.2 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203294/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[598,608,1332,1355]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
. Combined length of pronotum and elytra= 
<quantity box="[1099,1230,1332,1355]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="1.6" valueMin="1.4">1.4-1.6 mm</quantity>
; maximal pronotal width= 
<number box="[233,246,1367,1390]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" value="1.0">1</number>
<quantity box="[260,345,1367,1390]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="1.1">1.1 mm</quantity>
. Body dark brown with pronotum, antennae, legs, mentum and maxillary palpi somewhat paler; scape, pedicel and antennomeres 1, 2 and 
<number box="[552,578,1401,1424]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" value="11.0">11</number>
paler than antennomeres 
<number box="[869,882,1401,1424]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" value="3.0">3</number>
<number box="[896,926,1401,1424]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" value="10.0">10</number>
. Dorsal pubescence fairly uniform, denser on pronotum than on elytron and abdomen; frontal setae directed forward, median area of frons less dense than on vertex; pronotum, elytra and abdomen with pubescence oriented posteriorly, elytral setae curved and recumbent, becoming denser near humeral area and with interspaces as wide as puncture diameters, abdominal pubescence becoming denser on lateral margins of tergites. Metasternal punctation deep with its median line almost impunctate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1193,1979]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">
Anterior margin of head non-truncate, nearly rounded. Temple rounded to subquadrate in dorsal view. Submentum surface weakly convex. Antenna filiform, 
<number box="[612,645,1610,1633]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" value="2.6">2.6</number>
<number box="[659,692,1610,1633]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" value="2.8">2.8</number>
times longer than pronotum; with scape and pedicel sub-cylindrical and not flattened, segment 
<number box="[448,461,1644,1667]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" value="4.0">4</number>
symmetrical and narrower than the remaining antennomeres which increase gradually in width, from segment 
<number box="[379,392,1679,1702]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" value="5.0">5</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[407,473,1679,1702]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1673,1696]" captionTargetBox="[211,1370,260,1552]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,194,1649]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Megarthrus andinus sp. nov. Habitus (scale bar = 1 mm) (1); antenna (2); medial process of abdominal sternites II and III, in lateral view (anterior to left) (3); male sternite VIII, dissected (4); ventral (5) and lateral (6) aedeagus; female sternite VIII (7); ventral (8) and lateral (9) female genital segment (scale bars = 0.2 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203294/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[457,473,1679,1702]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1193,1979]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">
Pronotum 
<number box="[310,343,1714,1737]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" value="1.1">1.1</number>
times longer than head; median portion convex with medial groove impunctate and flat. Pronotal disc shallowly depressed along basal and apical portion of lateral edge which is more deeply depressed medially. Hypomeron smooth with its inner edge wider in its median portion. Prosternal medial ridge absent; anterior prosternal margin bordered with a regular row of five longitudinal ridges. Protrochanter lacking transverse ridge. Scutellum with anterior border rounded and posterior border slightly acute, margins raised and with pubescence oriented posteriorly. Elytra 
<number box="[1403,1436,1852,1875]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" value="2.1">2.1</number>
times longer than pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[466,529,1887,1910]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1673,1696]" captionTargetBox="[211,1370,260,1552]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,194,1649]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Megarthrus andinus sp. nov. Habitus (scale bar = 1 mm) (1); antenna (2); medial process of abdominal sternites II and III, in lateral view (anterior to left) (3); male sternite VIII, dissected (4); ventral (5) and lateral (6) aedeagus; female sternite VIII (7); ventral (8) and lateral (9) female genital segment (scale bars = 0.2 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203294/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[517,529,1887,1910]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
), weakly narrowed at base; humeral callus raised; disc with conspicuous swellings; anterior margin convex and inner apical angle obtuse. Abdominal sternites II and III with medial processes as in 
<figureCitation box="[1366,1431,1922,1945]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1673,1696]" captionTargetBox="[211,1370,260,1552]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,194,1649]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Megarthrus andinus sp. nov. Habitus (scale bar = 1 mm) (1); antenna (2); medial process of abdominal sternites II and III, in lateral view (anterior to left) (3); male sternite VIII, dissected (4); ventral (5) and lateral (6) aedeagus; female sternite VIII (7); ventral (8) and lateral (9) female genital segment (scale bars = 0.2 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203294/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[1416,1431,1922,1945]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[151,204,1956,1979]" name="India" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">Hind</collectingCountry>
wings fully developed.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203294/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" targetBox="[211,1370,260,1552]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1673,1758]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,314,1673,1696]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">FIGURES 1–9.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[319,525,1674,1696]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andinus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[319,525,1674,1696]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Megarthrus andinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[531,611,1674,1695]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[531,611,1674,1695]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Habitus (scale bar=1 mm) (1); antenna (2); medial process of abdominal sternites II and III, in lateral view (anterior to left) (3); male sternite VIII, dissected (4); ventral (5) and lateral (6) aedeagus; female sternite VIII (7); ventral (8) and lateral (9) female genital segment (scale bars= 0.2 mm).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1827,2023]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis box="[199,263,1827,1850]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Male:</emphasis>
Frontoclypeal area not modified. Protarsamere 
<number box="[812,825,1827,1850]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="1.0">1</number>
lacking adhesive setae. Mesofemur about as long as metafemur. Mesotibia shorter than metatibia. Metatarsomere 
<number box="[882,895,1862,1885]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="1.0">1</number>
somewhat shorter than combined length of metatarsomeres 
<number box="[325,338,1896,1919]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="2.0">2</number>
<number box="[351,367,1896,1919]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="4.0">4</number>
. Peg-like setae arranged in a single row on mesotrochanter, mesotibia and metatibia. Sternite VIII as in 
<figureCitation box="[178,243,1931,1954]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1673,1696]" captionTargetBox="[211,1370,260,1552]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,194,1649]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Megarthrus andinus sp. nov. Habitus (scale bar = 1 mm) (1); antenna (2); medial process of abdominal sternites II and III, in lateral view (anterior to left) (3); male sternite VIII, dissected (4); ventral (5) and lateral (6) aedeagus; female sternite VIII (7); ventral (8) and lateral (9) female genital segment (scale bars = 0.2 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203294/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number box="[227,243,1931,1954]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
. Sternite IX lacking subbasal protuberance. Aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation box="[884,979,1931,1954]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1673,1696]" captionTargetBox="[211,1370,260,1552]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,194,1649]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Megarthrus andinus sp. nov. Habitus (scale bar = 1 mm) (1); antenna (2); medial process of abdominal sternites II and III, in lateral view (anterior to left) (3); male sternite VIII, dissected (4); ventral (5) and lateral (6) aedeagus; female sternite VIII (7); ventral (8) and lateral (9) female genital segment (scale bars = 0.2 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203294/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Figs 5, 6</figureCitation>
. 
<emphasis box="[990,1070,1931,1954]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Female</emphasis>
: Abdominal tergite VIII lacking a medioapical projection. Sternite VIII as in 
<figureCitation box="[607,671,1966,1989]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1673,1696]" captionTargetBox="[211,1370,260,1552]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,194,1649]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Megarthrus andinus sp. nov. Habitus (scale bar = 1 mm) (1); antenna (2); medial process of abdominal sternites II and III, in lateral view (anterior to left) (3); male sternite VIII, dissected (4); ventral (5) and lateral (6) aedeagus; female sternite VIII (7); ventral (8) and lateral (9) female genital segment (scale bars = 0.2 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203294/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number box="[655,671,1966,1989]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
. Genital segment as in 
<figureCitation box="[918,1013,1966,1989]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1673,1696]" captionTargetBox="[211,1370,260,1552]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,194,1649]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Megarthrus andinus sp. nov. Habitus (scale bar = 1 mm) (1); antenna (2); medial process of abdominal sternites II and III, in lateral view (anterior to left) (3); male sternite VIII, dissected (4); ventral (5) and lateral (6) aedeagus; female sternite VIII (7); ventral (8) and lateral (9) female genital segment (scale bars = 0.2 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203294/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Figs 
<number box="[971,984,1966,1989]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="8.0">8</number>
<number box="[997,1013,1966,1989]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
; gonocoxal plate lacking a mediodorsal ridge.
</paragraph>
